To the Senior Management / Grievance Officer at Pharmeasy,

I am writing this email in a state of extreme distress and anger regarding
the appalling lack of empathy and professional ethics displayed by your
team regarding two orders placed for my 4-year-old daughter.

*Order Numbers:* 655498504036679680 & 655449478663073792

This has been a harrowing experience of lies, delays, and unprofessionalism.

I placed these orders yesterday, Dec 4th. For one order, I specifically
paid extra for *Express Delivery*, with a promised time of 6:00 PM. The
other was promised by 10:00 PM. Instead of delivering the medicine, your
system updated the status to *"Delivery delayed based on customer request."*

This is a blatant lie. I never requested a delay. Why would I pay for
Express delivery for my sick child and then ask you to delay it? This is
gaslighting at its finest. I called your support team at 5:18 PM yesterday
to correct this. The agent assured me she was raising a complaint and that
I would receive the order that night. That was another broken promise.

Today, the status showed "Out for Delivery" between 9:30 AM – 2:30 PM.
Desperate to get the medicine, I called the delivery executive directly.

   -

   I explained this is for a 4-year-old and requested early delivery.
   -

   He refused. He bluntly stated he would not deliver before 1:00 PM.
   -

   Helpless, I agreed and asked him to come as soon as possible after 1:00
   PM.

The 2:30 PM deadline passed with no delivery. I called your support line
again—no resolution, only assurances and promises. I called the delivery
executive repeatedly, and he ignored my calls.

Finally, at 3:16 PM today, he answered. He claimed he had "bike issues" and
was "nearby." When I simply asked him for a specific time so I could stop
waiting in anxiety, *he disconnected the call on me.*

You are not delivering a pair of shoes or a gadget; you are handling
healthcare. My 4-year-old child needs this medication. I paid for speed, I
paid for convenience, and instead, I have spent the last 24 hours chasing
your support team and being hung up on by your drivers.

You have taken my money, lied about my delivery preferences to cover your
operational failures, and left a parent helpless while their child waits
for medicine.

I demand the following immediately:

   1.

   Immediate delivery of these orders within the next hour.
   2.

   A full explanation as to why the status was falsely marked as "customer
   requested delay.

Please do not send me a templated apology. I need this escalated
immediately.

Regards
Tathagata Kandar
Marketeer
